This paper deals with the problem of place recognition, which is a task related to computer vision and robotics. The use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) to generate appearance of one domain from another is a technique commonly used in computer vision, which suggests that the paper belongs to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also deals with the task of Simultaneous Localization And Mapping (SLAM), which is a topic related to robotics, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to learn meaningful feature spaces for each domain, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper addresses a challenging perception task, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing and generation, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
